headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 28 points, Jrue Holiday added 25 and the Boston Celtics pulled away in the fourth quarter to beat the freefalling Miami Heat 103-91 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics add to Miami's misery, pull away in 4th for a 103-91 win over Heat

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 17 of his 27 points in the second half, and the Indiana Pacers beat the Philadelphia 76ers 112-100 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 27 points and helps Pacers rally with big second half to beat the 76ers 112-100

headlines.description: — James Harden and Kawhi Leonard each scored 25 points, with Harden scoring 13 in a dominant third quarter for Los Angeles, and the Clippers beat the Atlanta Hawks 121-98 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden, Leonard each score 25 points as Clippers ride lopsided 3rd quarter to 121-97 win over Hawks

headlines.description: — Tari Eason scored a career-high 30 points to lead the Houston Rockets to an easy 133-96 win over the Dallas Mavericks Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Eason's career-high 30 helps Houston Rockets extend win streak to 5 games with rout of Dallas

headlines.description: — Evan Mobley had 22 points and 11 rebounds, Darius Garland added 20 points and nine assists and the Cleveland Cavaliers recorded a franchise-record 16th straight victory with a 133-124 win over the Memphis Grizzlies on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mobley helps Cavs win franchise-record 16th straight, beat Grizzlies 133-124

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 28 points and the Minnesota Timberwolves rallied to beat the Orlando Magic 118-111 on Friday night for their seventh straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves rally to beat Magic 118-111 for their 7th straight victory

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball had 27 points and 14 assists, and the Charlotte Hornets made a franchise-record 26 3-pointers to roll past the San Antonio Spurs 145-134 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets make franchise-record 26 3s and Ball has 27 points and 14 assists in 145-134 win over Spurs

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray sank a 3-pointer with 5.6 seconds left and Russell Westbrook stole the inbounds pass for a exclamation-point dunk as the Denver Nuggets rebuffed the scrappy, short-handed Los Angeles Lakers 131-126 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jamal Murray's clutch 3-pointer helps Nuggets hold off short-handed Lakers 131-126

headlines.description: — Scottie Barnes had 20 points and 10 rebounds, Immanuel Quickley also scored 20 points and the Toronto Raptors beat the Utah Jazz 126-118 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes and Quickley each score 20 points to help Raptors beat Jazz, 126-118

headlines.description: — Devin Booker had 22 points and 13 assists, Kevin Durant also scored 22 points and the Phoenix Suns beat the Sacramento Kings 122-106 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker and Durant each score 22 points as Suns beat Kings 122-106
